params.authorizer_: The address of the new authorizer module, for which the update is canceled.

params.fundingManager_: The address of the new funding manager module, for which the update is canceled.

cancelModuleUpdate(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails if module update has not been initiated.

params.paymentProcessor_: The address of the new payment processro module, for which the update is canceled.

executeAddModule(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails if adding of module has not been initiated.Fails if timelock has not been expired yet.

executeRemoveModule(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails if removing of module has not been initiated.Fails if timelock has not been expired yet.

params.moduleFactory_: The address of the module factory.
params.modules: The addresses of the modules used in the {Orchestrator_v1}.
params.paymentProcessor: The address of the payment processor module.

initiateAddModuleWithTimelock(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails of adding module exeeds max modules limit.Fails if address invalid or address already added as module.

initiateRemoveModuleWithTimelock(address.details: Reverts if module to be removed is the current authorizer/fundingManager/paymentProcessor.         The functions specific to updating these 3 module categories should be used instead.Only callable by authorized address.Fails if address not added as module.

params.authorizer_: The address of the new authorizer module.

params.fundingManager_: The address of the new funding manager module.

params.paymentProcessor_: The address of the new payment processor module.

returns._0: True if module added, false otherwise.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Because we want to expose the `isTrustedForwarder` function from the {ERC2771Context} Contract in the         {IOrchestrator_v1} we have to override it here as the original openzeppelin version doesnt contain an         interface that we could use to expose it.

returns._0: True if the address is the trusted forwarder, false otherwise.

authorizer().notice: The {IAuthorizer_v1} implementation used to authorize addresses.

cancelAuthorizerUpdate(address).notice: Cancels the replacement of the current authorizer with `authorizer_`.

cancelFundingManagerUpdate(address).notice: Cancels the replacement of the current funding manager with `fundingManager_`.

cancelModuleUpdate(address).notice: Cancels an initiated update for a module. Can be adding or removing a module         from the {Orchestrator_v1}.

cancelPaymentProcessorUpdate(address).notice: Cancels the replacement of the current payment processor with `paymentProcessor_`.

executeSetAuthorizer(address).notice: Executes replacing the current authorizer with `_authorizer`.!!! IMPORTANT !!! When changing the Authorizer the current set of assigned addresses to Roles are lost.         Make sure initial owners are set properly.

executeSetFundingManager(address).notice: Executes replaces the current funding manager with `fundingManager_`.!!! IMPORTANT !!! When changing the FundingManager the current funds still contained in the module might         not be retrievable. Make sure to clean the FundingManager properly beforehand.

executeSetPaymentProcessor(address).notice: Executes replaces the current payment processor with `paymentProcessor_`.!!! IMPORTANT !!! When changing the PaymentProcessor the current ongoing payment orders are lost.         Make sure to resolve those payments properly beforehand.

fundingManager().notice: The {IFundingManager_v1} implementation used to hold and distribute Funds.

governor().notice: The {IGovernor_v1} implementation used for protocol level interactions.

initiateAddModuleWithTimelock(address).notice: Initiates the adding of a module to the {Orchestrator_v1} on a timelock.

initiateRemoveModuleWithTimelock(address.notice: Initiate the removal of a module from the {Orchestrator_v1} on a timelock.

initiateSetAuthorizerWithTimelock(addres.notice: Initiates replacing the current authorizer with `_authorizer` on a timelock.

initiateSetFundingManagerWithTimelock(ad.notice: Initiates replaces the current funding manager with `fundingManager_` on a timelock.

initiateSetPaymentProcessorWithTimelock(.notice: Initiates replaces the current payment processor with `paymentProcessor_` on a timelock.

isModule(address).notice: Returns whether the address `module` is added as module.

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: Returns wether the given address is the trusted forwarder or not.

listModules().notice: Returns the list of all modules.

paymentProcessor().notice: The {IPaymentProcessor_v1} implementation used to process module         payments.

trustedForwarder().notice: Returns the trusted forwarder for metatransactions.
